## Variants

### Tabs

```html
<ul class="nav nav-tabs">
  <li class="nav-item">
    <a class="nav-link active" href="#">Tab 1</a>
  </li>
  <li class="nav-item">
    <a class="nav-link" href="#">Tab 2</a>
  </li>
</ul>
```

### Pills

```html
<ul class="nav nav-pills">
  <li class="nav-item">
    <a class="nav-link active" href="#">Pill 1</a>
  </li>
  <li class="nav-item">
    <a class="nav-link" href="#">Pill 2</a>
  </li>
</ul>
```

## Accessibility Notes

- Use semantic elements: `<nav>` tag or `<ul>`/`<li>` if it's a list of links.
- Use `aria-current="page"` or visually highlight the active link.
- Ensure color contrast for active/inactive states.

```html
<nav aria-label="Main navigation">
  <ul class="nav nav-pills">
    <li class="nav-item">
      <a class="nav-link" aria-current="page" href="#">Home</a>
    </li>
    ...
  </ul>
</nav>
``` 